<p class="comments-byline">
        
        <strong><cite>Chris Brossard</cite></strong>
         July 26th, 2007                
        
      <p>Guy,<br />
Congrats to you and the team at LinkedIn.  I call it Facebook for adults with jobs.  While LinkedIn is a great concept, I wonder if we couldn&#8217;t improve the stickiness by incorporating Yelp-like functionality.  I realize that we can recommend each other, but frankly the recommendations appear to be a bit glib and superficial. And there is no apparent way to provide constructive or reasoned, critical feedback. If LinkedIn became a bona fide source of serious, critical reviews of people and companies both positive and not so positive I believe its usefulness would be enhanced tremendously.</p>

    </li>

  
      
        

