<p class="comments-byline">
        
        <strong><cite>Robin Ogden</cite></strong>
         July 30th, 2007                
        
      <p>Great comment Ido &#8211; I agree it would be extremely helpful if there was a scale that you chose from that indicated how well you were really &#8216;linkedin&#8217; with the individual you accept an invitation from.  Even though you can deny an invite, that is just and either/or option.  Better would be one where you could choose on a scale of 1 &#8211; 5 (5 meaning a close contact you know well personally, and so on&#8230;).  This would help those who view other profiles to know when they might have a &#8216;real&#8217; second level connection or if it is just someone their link met at a meeting.</p>
<p>Robin Ogden<br />
<a href="http://www.firedupcareers.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.firedupcareers.com</a></p>

